It is understood the pupils had eaten sweets given to them by an unknown man the previous day. JOHANNESBURG - At least 20 pupils have been rushed to hospital after complaining of stomach cramps, nausea and vomiting at the Suidheuwels Primary School, south of Johannesburg. It s understood the pupils had eaten sweets given to them by an unknown man the previous day.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said: The children told paramedics they had apparently been given sweets by an unknown man the previous day. Local authorities will be investigating further. We urge all parents to teach their kids not to accept sweets from strangers. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)